<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">660f.116Auto/36: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gittings</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-13T13:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">October 13,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 13—9:45
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>74. Your telegram No. 47, October 11, 5 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d714fn54">Not printed.</note> Note as amended therein has
                            been presented today. Reference to road tax was left in note. Every
                            effort will be made to achieve results.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gittings</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>